|---|---|---|
| A01 – Broken Access Control | 🔴 No auth on `/users` | #4, #5 |
| A02 – Cryptographic Failures | 🟠 PII in plaintext | #4 |
| A03 – Injection | 🟢 No dynamic queries (yet) | — |
| A04 – Insecure Design | 🔴 No rate limiting | #3 |
| A05 – Security Misconfiguration | 🔴 No security headers, stack trace leak | #2, #6, #7 |
| A06 – Vulnerable Components | 🟠 No package.json/audit | #10 |
| A07 – Auth Failures | 🔴 No authentication at all | #4 |
| A08 – Data Integrity Failures | 🟢 N/A for current scope | — |
| A09 – Logging Failures | 🟡 No request logging | #9 |
| A10 – SSRF | 🟢 No outbound requests | — |

**Bottom line:** The app is safe from injection (A03) only because it has no database or dynamic queries *yet*. The biggest immediate risks are **no access control** on user data and **no security headers**. Adding `helmet`, `cors`, rate limiting, and authentication middleware would address the critical gaps.---

